{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Xqga96m5UvUWHQN1y2XPdM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The certs mounted are: ca.crt, node.crt, node.key. But for the client cert (root), we need `client.root.crt` and `client.root.key` in the certs directory. These are currently not there - the node secret only has node certs.\n\nThe goal is to run:\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs -e \"SELECT 1;\"\n```\n\nThis requires ca.crt, client.root.crt, and client.root.key to be in /cockroach/cockroach-certs.\nI'm considering a few approaches: creating a combined secret with all the certificates, mounting multiple secrets at the same path, copying certs at startup, or using an init container. The cleanest solution is to create a new secret that bundles all the needed files together - ca.crt, node.crt, node.key, client.root.crt, and client.root.key - and mount that single secret to the pod.\n\nI should note that in production, client certs shouldn't live on the node pods, but for testing this approach works fine. Now I'll create the combined secret and update the StatefulSet to use it.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":463,"cache_read_input_tokens":41447,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":463},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab62093c-ef76-453f-83cd-84d3752ec3fa","uuid":"693bab36-2c5a-48eb-90e6-1a587185437b","request_id":"req_011Cc5ESTmWBqLNCQa6H5QdV"}
